 =?UTF-8?q?SDLDBG.LOG?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Wave 13.6.1's primary patch 0023 made RING_BUFFER_CHUNKS env-var-controlled
to allow a 4-config keyboard-regression bisect in a single CF-card swap.
The .bat-driven bisect would have to REN logs between configs to avoid
DOSKUTSU.EXE truncating each prior run's data on next launch — and that
rename pattern has freeze edge cases (if the keyboard locks before .bat's
post-rename runs, logs land at SDLDBG.LOG and need pre-rename in the next
.bat).

This patch makes the SDL trace path overridable via DOSKUTSU_LOG_TAG. When
set, default becomes /DOSKUTSU/<TAG>SDL.LOG; when unset, default is
/DOSKUTSU/sdldbg.log. Each .bat just SETs DOSKUTSU_LOG_TAG=R1/R2/R3/R4 and
the runs land directly at unique paths — no rename, no freeze edge case.

Also moves the default location from C:\ root to C:\DOSKUTSU\ so SDL trace
lives alongside engine DEBUG.LOG. Single directory to scp from after a
real-HW iter.

Pairs with engine-side patch 0069 which honours the same env var for
DEBUG.LOG → <TAG>.LOG (already lives in C:\DOSKUTSU\ via getPrefPath).

Tag length: <TAG>SDL.LOG must fit DOS 8.3, so tag should be ≤5 chars
(R1..R9 fits; longer tags get truncated by FAT12/16 short-name handling).
Strict-match: any non-empty value used as-is; empty/unset → default.

See docs/PHASE9-WAVE-14-PLAN.md §2 for the wave 13.6.1 bisect design.
---
 src/video/dos/SDL_dosdbg.c | 27 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++-
 1 file changed, 26 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosdbg.c b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosdbg.c
index eaf34399d..26e38484a 100644
--- a/src/video/dos/SDL_dosdbg.c
+++ b/src/video/dos/SDL_dosdbg.c
@@ -42,11 +42,36 @@
 // See SDL_dosdbg.h for rationale (gateway4 wave 1 log-race postmortem,
 // docs/PHASE9-15FPS-PLAN.md §3 Lever 1 wave 2 plan).
 static FILE *g_dbg_log = NULL;
+static char g_dbg_log_path[64];
+
+// DOSKUTSU patch (Phase 9 wave 13.6.1): the log-file path is overridable via
+// the DOSKUTSU_LOG_TAG env var so a multi-config bisect can write each run's
+// SDL trace to a unique filename without renames between runs. The log lives
+// in the doskutsu game directory alongside DEBUG.LOG (rather than at the CF
+// root) — single dir to scp from after a real-HW iter. When unset
+// (empty/null), default "/DOSKUTSU/sdldbg.log" is used. When set to e.g.
+// "R1", the SDL trace goes to "/DOSKUTSU/R1SDL.LOG". Tag should be short
+// enough that "<TAG>SDL.LOG" fits DOS 8.3 (so max 5 chars). Strict match:
+// any non-empty value is used as-is; we don't try to validate.
+static const char *doskutsu_dbg_resolve_path(void)
+{
+    if (g_dbg_log_path[0] == '\0') {
+        const char *tag = SDL_getenv("DOSKUTSU_LOG_TAG");
+        if (tag && tag[0] != '\0') {
+            SDL_snprintf(g_dbg_log_path, sizeof(g_dbg_log_path),
+                         "/DOSKUTSU/%sSDL.LOG", tag);
+        } else {
+            SDL_strlcpy(g_dbg_log_path, "/DOSKUTSU/sdldbg.log",
+                        sizeof(g_dbg_log_path));
+        }
+    }
+    return g_dbg_log_path;
+}
 
 void doskutsu_dbg_open(void)
 {
     if (!g_dbg_log) {
-        g_dbg_log = fopen("/sdldbg.log", "wb");
+        g_dbg_log = fopen(doskutsu_dbg_resolve_path(), "wb");
     }
 }
 
